🜁 Alchemist Exchange Library (AEL)

“Don’t store value. Circulate it.”

⸻

🧭 Overview

Alchemist Exchange Library (AEL) is a system that transforms physical assets into circulating value.

Users deposit items → AI appraises them → value is converted into credits → credits unlock access to other items in a shared custodial library.

Ownership becomes optional.
Access becomes fluid.
Value is conserved, not trapped.

⸻

⚙️ Core Flow

1. Deposit (Input → Structure)
	•	User submits an asset (e.g., LEGO set, Pokémon card, tool)
	•	System records identity, condition, completeness

2. Appraisal (Alchemist Layer)
	•	AI evaluates:
	•	condition
	•	completeness
	•	rarity
	•	demand/liquidity
	•	market comps
	•	Outputs a credit value

⸻

3. Credit Issuance (Flow Layer)
	•	User receives credits based on appraised value
	•	Credits are:
	•	backed by real inventory
	•	visible and auditable
	•	conserved across the system

⸻

4. Custody (Library Layer)
	•	Asset is stored in secure, trackable inventory
	•	Tagged, scanned, and logged in custody ledger

⸻

5. Access / Exchange
	•	User browses inventory
	•	Uses credits to:
	•	borrow
	•	exchange
	•	reserve
	•	redeem

⸻

6. Return / Settlement
	•	Items returned → credits restored
	•	Damage or loss → credit penalties applied

⸻

🧱 System Architecture

🜂 Alchemist (Appraisal Engine)
	•	AI valuation system
	•	Converts objects → structured value
	•	Hybrid AI + human audit

⸻

📚 Library (Custodial Layer)
	•	Storage, cataloging, and retrieval
	•	Chain-of-custody tracking
	•	Warehouse or distributed nodes

⸻

🔁 Exchange (Credit Layer)
	•	Ledger-backed credit system
	•	Controls issuance, locking, and redemption
	•	Ensures conservation of value

⸻

